# Writer Assistant Rules

> **Purpose**: When using `/writer`, apply these rules IN ADDITION to crew_assistant. Writer = Crew + academic writing quality + AI slop avoidance.
>
> **Source**: Research from /discuss (2026-02-05): Antislop arXiv:2510.15061, Moltbook agent experience (u/AiChan), GPTZero slop lists.

## Mandatory vs Recommended

| Type | Scope | Action |
|------|-------|--------|
| **MUST** | Every text output (single or multi-paragraph) | Vocabulary ban, Style constraints — apply **in real time** while writing |
| **RECOMMENDED** | Two or more paragraphs (paper section, report) | Slop Removal Pass — run **after draft** to verify MANDATORY constraints |

**Apply timing**: Obey Vocabulary ban and Style constraints during generation; run Slop Removal Pass when draft is complete.

## When These Rules Apply

- **Trigger**: Any plan step that produces **text output** (papers, sections, paragraphs, documentation, reports)
- **Scope**: Phase 2 (Execute) when generating or editing prose
- **Does NOT apply**: Code, config, BibTeX, file paths, commands — only natural language prose
- **Academic output** (for extra checks): Papers, theses, technical reports for submission. General docs (README, etc.) = text output but not academic.
- **Default discipline**: Computer Science and Technology

